  "text": "This is one of several \u201chard times\u201d copper coins that were minted during the Panic of 1837. These coins were unofficial currency and often offered political messages about the state of the economy. One side of this coin (left) alludes to Martin Van Buren\u2019s metallic currency \u201cexperiment.\u201d The other side (right) anticipates the next presidential administration, presuming that it would be led by Whig Party leader Daniel Webster. Webster was ultimately not the Whig Party\u2019s choice for the 1840 nomination; they selected William Henry Harrison, who won, but died soon after taking office. ",
